    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're a content creator working on a video intro. You always start your videos with the same catchphrase, but right now, the code repeats the line three times using copy/paste. Clean it up by putting your signature intro into a function so you can reuse it anywhere in your content.\r\n\r\n1. Look at the three repeated lines of code.\r\n\r\n2. Define a function called `intro_line()` that prints the catchphrase once.\r\n\r\n3. Replace the repeated code by calling your function three times.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nPay close attention to indentation, and use the UMPIRE strategy:\r\n\r\n* **U**nderstand: What message are you repeating?\r\n\r\n* **M**ake a plan: Which messages go in which function?\r\n\r\n* **P**roduce: Write and call both functions.\r\n\r\n* **I**nspect: Does it run as expected?\r\n\r\n* **E**xplain: How did using functions improve the code?",
